# DICTOGLOSS — DATABASE SCHEMA REFERENCE

Agents must rely on this document before any database-related code. Do not invent field names or relations — only what is defined below.

## MODELS

### User

- `id`: String `@id` `@default(cuid())`
- `email`: String `@unique`
- `password`: String (bcrypt, minimum 12 rounds)
- `name`: String
- `role`: `Role` (ADMIN | STUDENT)
- `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `deletedAt` (soft delete)
- relations: `lessons[]`, `attempts[]`

### Lesson

- `id`: String `@id` `@default(cuid())`
- `title`: String
- `shareToken`: String `@unique` (public token in the URL)
- `userId`: String (FK → User, teacher who created the lesson)
- `voice`: String (OpenAI voices: alloy, echo, fable, onyx, nova, shimmer)
- `accent`: String (`american` | `british` — display only)
- `isActive`: Boolean `@default(true)`
- `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `deletedAt`
- relations: `sentences[]`, `attempts[]`

### Sentence

- `id`: String `@id` `@default(cuid())`
- `lessonId`: String (FK → Lesson)
- `order`: Int (starts at 1, playback order)
- `text`: String (correct answer — **never** send to the client until the answer is checked)
- `audioUrl`: String? (URL in DO Spaces after generation)
- `audioStatus`: `AudioStatus` (PENDING | PROCESSING | READY | FAILED)
- `createdAt`, `updatedAt`
- relations: `answers[]`

### LessonAttempt

- `id`: String `@id` `@default(cuid())`
- `lessonId`: String (FK → Lesson)
- `userId`: String? (null for anonymous students)
- `studentName`: String (entered before start)
- `startedAt`: DateTime `@default(now())`
- `completedAt`: DateTime?
- `totalScore`: Int? (number of correct answers)
- `totalCount`: Int? (number of sentences)
- relations: `answers[]`

### StudentAnswer

- `id`: String `@id` `@default(cuid())`
- `attemptId`: String (FK → LessonAttempt)
- `sentenceId`: String (FK → Sentence)
- `studentText`: String (student input)
- `isCorrect`: Boolean
- `playCount`: Int `@default(0)` (maximum 3)
- `answeredAt`: DateTime `@default(now())`

## ENUMS

- `Role`: ADMIN | STUDENT
- `AudioStatus`: PENDING | PROCESSING | READY | FAILED

## CRITICAL RULES

- Do not return `Sentence.text` to the client until the answer is submitted and checked.
- Enforce `playCount` limit of 3 on the server, not only in the UI.
- Answer check: `studentText.trim() === sentence.text.trim()` — exact match; case and punctuation matter.
- Soft delete: always use `deletedAt`; do not hard-delete entities that use soft delete.
- Public lesson identifier is only `shareToken`; do not use `lesson.id` in student-facing URLs.
